article.headline: San Diego 74, San Jose State 60
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Brice Vounang scored 15 of his game-high 25 points in the second half to help San Diego end a 23-game road losing streak with a 74-60 victory over San Jose State on Tuesday night. Nick Lewis added 15 points as the Toreros (3-4) snapped a four-game losing streak overall. Brett Melton had 13 points. Michael McFadden, Marquin Chandler and Alex Elam each scored 14 points for San Jose State (3-3), which lost for the second time in three games. San Diego lost at home 71-10 to the Spartans 10 days ago when it failed to convert four three throws in the closing minutes. The Toreros won on the road for the first time since an 81-63 victory at San Francisco on Feb. 22, 2003. Vounang, who reached double figures in scoring for the 14th straight game, made three quick baskets to start the second half as San Diego went on a 15-3 run to grab a 43-31 lead with 14:10 remaining. He made his first seven shots of the second half. The Toreros eventually built a 15-point advantage. McFadden's 3-pointer with 5:43 remaining drew the Spartans within 61-54 but that was as close as they came. Turnovers plagued both teams, combining for 38. The Toreros grabbed an early 20-10 lead, but the Spartans outscored San Diego 18-8 the rest of the way to tie the game by halftime at 28. Kareem Guilbeaux scored the tying basket with 33 seconds in the half.
